<br>
Think about it - Slows are basically the single most crippling ability against mobs in this game, and VI knows it. They wrote the AI in such a way that trying to slow a mob (even if it is resisted, did not take hold, etc) generates a large amount of aggro. Which is exactly why weapons with a slow proc are popular as aggro grabbers.<br>
<br>
Debuffs work the same way, perhaps to a different degree than slows, but we all know how badly enchanters can grab aggro with tash.<br>
